Data science education is still new to young learners. Based on the increasing number of calls for accessible data science education implementations from local districts and states, we developed a physical movement and data science unit for a fifth-grade computer science course. The inclusion of sports resonates with goals to broaden participation in computing fields by highlighting how computational knowledge can be applied to the real-world beyond classrooms. We implemented SportSense for Data Literacy, which is an 8 week sports and data curriculum for fifth-grade students to learn and practice data processes for collecting and interpreting their personal physical movement. This paper covers SportSense's motivations and goals, describing how this curriculum met these metrics in our implementation across 32 classrooms in the spring of 2025.